5000|$|In the west, {{the first}} {{prominent}} moral sense theory {{is found in}} Anthony Ashley-Cooper, 3rd Earl of Shaftesbury (1671-1713). His major work espousing a form of moral sense theory is An Inquiry Concerning Virtue, or Merit (first published in an <b>unauthorized</b> <b>edition</b> in 1699).|$|E
